    faqs: [{"id":"faq-0","question":"Is our data encrypted?","answer":"Absolutely. All data is protected with military-grade AES-256 encryption at rest and TLS 1.3 encryption in transit. Our zero-knowledge architecture means that even our own engineers cannot access your data. We undergo regular third-party penetration testing and maintain SOC 2 Type II certification to ensure the highest security standards are met continuously."},{"id":"faq-1","question":"Are you SOC 2 Type II certified?","answer":"Yes, TrackNexus maintains active compliance certifications including SOC 2 Type II, GDPR, HIPAA, and ISO 27001. We conduct annual third-party audits and continuous monitoring to ensure ongoing compliance. Our dedicated compliance team stays ahead of regulatory changes and updates our platform proactively so you always meet the latest requirements."},{"id":"faq-2","question":"Where is data stored?","answer":"Your data is stored in Tier IV certified data centers with multi-region redundancy across the US, EU, and APAC. You can choose your primary data region to comply with data residency requirements. All data is replicated in real time across multiple availability zones, ensuring 99.99% uptime and disaster recovery with less than 15-minute recovery point objectives."},{"id":"faq-3","question":"What is your response time?","answer":"Our support team is available 24/7 with guaranteed response times. Priority support customers receive responses within 1 hour, while standard support guarantees a 4-hour response window. Enterprise customers get a dedicated account manager and direct access to our engineering team for complex issues. We also offer comprehensive self-service resources including documentation, video tutorials, and an active community forum."}],
