    faqs: [{"id":"faq-0","question":"What integrations are available?","answer":"TrackNexus integrates with over 100 popular business applications out of the box, including Slack, Microsoft Teams, Salesforce, HubSpot, Zapier, Jira, Asana, QuickBooks, and many more. Our open API and webhook system make it easy to build custom integrations with any platform. New integrations are added every month based on customer requests, and our integration team can build custom connectors for enterprise customers at no additional cost."},{"id":"faq-1","question":"Can you connect to our legacy systems?","answer":"Yes, our integration engineering team specializes in connecting modern platforms with legacy systems. We support REST APIs, SOAP web services, FTP/SFTP file transfers, and database-level integrations. Our team has successfully connected TrackNexus with hundreds of legacy systems including SAP, Oracle, mainframe applications, and custom-built enterprise software. We handle the complexity so your team does not have to."},{"id":"faq-2","question":"How is data synced between systems?","answer":"Data synchronization happens in real time using our robust webhook system and event-driven architecture. Changes in TrackNexus are immediately reflected in connected systems, and vice versa. Our sync engine includes built-in conflict resolution, retry logic, and data validation to ensure no information is ever lost. You maintain full control over sync rules, frequency, and data mapping through our intuitive integration dashboard."},{"id":"faq-3","question":"What support options do you offer?","answer":"We provide multi-channel support through email, phone, and live chat, all available during extended business hours with 24/7 emergency support for critical issues. Enterprise plan customers receive a dedicated account manager who understands your organization's unique needs and provides proactive guidance. All customers have access to our comprehensive knowledge base, video tutorials, community forums, and regular webinars covering new features and best practices."}],
